Nigeria’s Lagos State Debt Reaches $793 Million, ThisDay Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-05-20T08:34:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-20/nigeria-s-lagos-state-debt-reaches-793-million-thisday-says.html
Nigeria ’s Lagos state, which includes
the country’s commercial capital, has debts of 124.2 billion
naira ($793 million),  ThisDay  reported, citing the state’s
commissioner of finance, Rotimi Oyekan.  External debt stood at 62.4 billion naira, while domestic
borrowing was 61.8 billion naira, the Lagos-based newspaper
said.  The state is using less than 30 percent of its total
revenue to manage the debt, ThisDay cited Oyekan as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 